  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Subjects must meet each one of the following inclusion criteria in order to be eligible for
        participation in the study:

          1. Be at least 21 years of age.

          2. Have a current (past 12 months) DSM-5 diagnosis of AUD.

          3. Have a BAC by breathalyzer equal to 0.000 when s/he signed the informed consent
             document (either just prior to or immediately after signing consent).

          4. Be seeking treatment for problems with alcohol.

        Additional will be evaluated in clinic.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        Evaluations will be conducted in clinic.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
